### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

forms

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

We have many places where our domain model can have undefined props which are mapped to some default values in the form model.

I wrote a small helper that uses a linkedSignal and an effect to map the domain to the form model and back (see https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/65194#issuecomment-3585154425 and also stack blitz below).

Now, when I apply this mapping, the code compiles fine, but as soon as I remove all text input from the input element, I get this error: `TypeError: this.field(...) is not a function`.

```typescript
interface Test {
  name?: string; // domain model: name is optional
}

interface FormModel {
  name: string; // form model: name is required (undefined is converted to empty string and back)
}

@Component({
  selector: 'some-component',
  template: `<input type="text" [field]="valueForm.name" />`,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [Field],
})
export class SomeComponent implements FormValueControl<FormModel> {
  public readonly value = model.required<FormModel>();
  protected readonly valueForm = form<FormModel>(this.value);
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: `<some-component [field]="valueForm"/>`,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [Field, SomeComponent],
})
export class App {
  protected readonly value = signal<Test | undefined>(undefined);
  protected readonly valueForm = mappedForm(this.value, {
    modelToForm: (modelValue) => {
      return {
        name: 'no name yet',
        ...modelValue,
      };
    },
    formToModel: (formValue) => {
      return {
        ...formValue,
        // Convert empty name to undefined
        name: formValue.name || undefined,
      };
    },
  });
}
```



