### Anything else?

I'm not sure which `field` (the error message refers to) is not a function. Would be nice if the error message would also tell at which component the error originally happens. I would guess that the undefined `name` of the domain model is involved here.

Or is there a bug on my side using the form?

See also https://stackoverflow.com/questions/79847618/angular-21-signal-forms-typeerror-this-field-is-not-a-function

### Feature Description

For the dialog in the Material component, I can customize the animation by adding a   `panelClass: "sidenav-dialog"` config in the typescript, and add the following styles in `styles.scss`:

```css
.sidenav-dialog {
    animation: enter 0.3s ease-in-out;

    .mdc-dialog--closing {
      animation: leave 0.3s ease-in-out;
    }
}
```

However, when I switch to the dialog in the CDK, the exit animation no longer works.

The dialog in the CDK component should have more flexibility in customization, such as specifying the CSS class name when exit.

